  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nFace ID authentication is currently only available on the login screen and can be enabled during onboarding. This feature should be extended to various functionalities across the app for better security and user experience. \r\n\r\n- [ ]  On **Join Community**: Display Face ID authentication instead of password Bottom Sheet when Face ID is available\r\n[View Figma Design](https://www.figma.com/file/Tf5nfkYvpbnNCo4rKLK7lS?node-id=5963:45899&mode=design#567168921)\r\n- [ ] Enable Face ID on **Sign Transaction** (will be implemented in scope of Wallet)\r\n- [ ] Enable Face ID on **Reaveling QRCode** [View Figma Design](https://www.figma.com/file/Tf5nfkYvpbnNCo4rKLK7lS/Feedback-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=3682-98959&mode=design&t=idJkYQmWH5Grsbno-0)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nFace ID is only available for login and can be enabled during the onboarding process. We need to add a centralized way to enable Face ID within the app.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n1. Add a centralized way to enable Face ID within the app (Profile > Post MVP?)\r\n2. Implement Face ID authentication for joining communities.\r\n3. Implement Face ID authentication for signing transactions.\r\n4. Implement Face ID authentication for revealing QR codes.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- [ ]  Face ID option is available and can be enabled from a centralized location within the app.\r\n- [ ]  When Face ID is enabled and available, the app shows Face ID authentication as an option instead of the password Bottom Sheet.\r\n- [ ]  Face ID authentication is functional and secure when joining a community.\r\n- [ ]  Face ID authentication is functional and secure for signing transactions.\r\n- [ ]  Face ID authentication is functional and secure for revealing QR codes.\r\n- [ ]  Appropriate fallback mechanisms are in place if Face ID authentication fails (e.g., revert to password or other secure methods).\r\n- [ ]  The feature works consistently across different devices that support Face ID.\r\n- [ ]  Unit and integration tests confirm that the feature works as expected.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nThis is considered a bigger issue and may require subdividing into smaller tasks for easier tracking and implementation.\r\n",
